  "issue_number": 1283,
  "issue_title": "[FEATURE] Add repo allocation breakdown to `gitt miner score`",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nAdd a per-repository emission allocation breakdown to `gitt miner score`.\n\nThe command should continue showing the final blended reward, but also expose which repository slices contributed to that reward, how each repo slice was split between PR scoring and issue discovery, and how much reward the miner received from each side.\n\n## Motivation\n\nAfter repo-bounded emission allocation, the final reward is no longer explained by a single normalized OSS score plus issue-discovery score. Rewards are now allocated through each repository\u2019s configured `emission_share`, with a per-repo split between PR scoring and issue discovery.\n\n`gitt miner score` already runs the production scoring pipeline locally, but it only reports the final scalar reward. That makes it hard for miners and contributors to understand why a reward changed, whether a specific repo slice capped the result, or how much came from PRs versus issue discovery.\n\nA repo allocation breakdown makes the local scoring tool match the current reward model and gives contributors a clear way to verify allocation behavior after changes to scoring or repository config.",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-26T16:46:37Z",
